citations:
    citation-agot-daenerys-v:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Daenerys V"
            text_from_source: "The heart was steaming in the cool evening air when Khal Drogo set it before her, raw and bloody. His arms were red to the elbow."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Daenerys eats the raw heart of a stallion in the ritual pit, proclaiming the child in her womb is a son. The crones of the dosh khaleen prophesy he will be the Stallion Who Mounts the World. Daenerys names him Rhaego, after her dead brother Rhaegar. Viserys arrives drunk and armed at the feast hall, drawing his sword inside Vaes Dothrak (a sacred prohibition). Khal Drogo fulfills his promise of a 'golden crown' by pouring molten gold over Viserys's head, killing him. Daenerys watches without weeping."
